  "scientificName": "Zingiber officinale",
  "family": "Zingiberaceae",
  "genus": "Zingiber",
  "description": {
    "en": "A flowering plant whose rhizome (ginger root) is widely used as a spice and folk medicine. Native to Maritime Southeast Asia.",
    "zh-Hant": "薑（學名：Zingiber officinale）是一種具有藥用價值的天然產物。現代藥理學研究證實其含有多種生物活性成分，在傳統醫學和現代保健領域均有重要應用價值。",
    "zh-Hans": "薑（学名：Zingiber officinale）是一种具有药用價值的天然產物。現代药理学研究证实其含有多种生物活性成分，在传统医学和現代保健領域均有重要应用價值。"
  },
  "commonName": {
    "en": "Common Ginger, True Ginger",
    "zh-Hant": "生薑",
    "hi": "अदरक",
    "zh-Hans": "姜"
  },
  "botanicalDescription": {
    "en": "Zingiber officinale is a herbaceous perennial growing 30-100 cm tall. The plant produces annual pseudostems from a horizontal rhizome. Leaves are lanceolate, 15-30 cm long. Flowers are pale yellow with purple edges, produced on dense spikes."
  },
  "geographicalDistribution": {
    "en": "Native to Southeast Asia. Widely cultivated in tropical and subtropical regions including India, China, Nigeria, and Jamaica."
  },
